p: To the Sheriff of King County Greeting:

In the name of the United States of America you are hereby commanded to take the body of James Riley "if to be found in your County" and him safely keep so that you have him before the District Court for Pierce County W.T. at a time to began and holden at Stulacoono in said County and Territory on the 21st day of September A.D. 1863 "the same being the third Monday in said month." then and there to answer on an indictment pending against him for assault with intent to kill
Herein Fail not and have you then and there you this writ with your days indorsed thereon
Witness the Hon C C Hewett Chief Justice of Washington Territory and presiding Judge of the District Court for Pierce County W.T. the 24th day of August A.D. 1863
